.TH DNS-UPDATE 1 "March 2026" "dns-update" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dns-update \- keep DNS A and AAAA records aligned with egress IP addresses
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dns-update
[\fB\-\-config\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB\-\-dry-run\fR]
[\fB\-\-validate-config\fR]
[\fB\-\-print-effective-config\fR]
[\fB\-\-timeout\fR \fIDURATION\fR]
[\fB\-\-verbose\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dns-update
probes the current IPv4 and IPv6 egress addresses of the local host and updates
the configured DNS A and AAAA records when the observed addresses differ from
the current provider state.
.P
The program is intended for timer-driven operation, including systemd timer
deployments. It supports dry-run execution, bounded retries, and provider
reconciliation against the live DNS record state before applying changes.
.P
In the packaged systemd deployment, the Cloudflare token source file is stored
at
.I /etc/dns-update/cloudflare.token
and is materialized into the service credential directory by
.BR LoadCredential= .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-config
Load configuration from the specified JSON file. If omitted and
.B DNS_UPDATE_CONFIG
is unset, the program first looks for
.I config.json
in the current working directory and then
.I /etc/dns-update/config.json .
.TP
.B \-\-dry-run
Print the changes that would be made without mutating DNS records.
.TP
.B \-\-validate-config
Validate the assembled configuration, print
.B config is valid
to standard output, and exit without contacting the DNS provider.
.TP
.B \-\-print-effective-config
Print the fully assembled effective configuration as JSON and exit without
contacting the DNS provider.
.TP
.B \-\-timeout
Apply a global execution timeout to the entire reconciliation run. A value of
.B 0
disables the global timeout.
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Enable verbose logging, including no-op status output.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B DNS_UPDATE_CONFIG
Path to the JSON configuration file. This has the same effect as
.BR \-\-config .
.TP
.B DNS_UPDATE_DRY_RUN
Boolean override for
.BR \-\-dry-run .
.TP
.B DNS_UPDATE_VERBOSE
Boolean override for
.BR \-\-verbose .
.TP
.B DNS_UPDATE_TIMEOUT
Duration override for
.BR \-\-timeout .
.TP
.B DNS_UPDATE_PROVIDER_CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN_FILE
Override only the configured Cloudflare token-file path. This is primarily used
by the packaged systemd service to point the binary at a systemd-managed
credential file.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/dns-update/config.json
Primary JSON configuration file for packaged and systemd deployments.
.TP
.I /etc/dns-update/cloudflare.token
Source file for the Cloudflare API token used by packaged systemd deployments.
.TP
.I /etc/dns-update/dns-update.env
Optional environment overrides for packaged systemd deployments.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B non-zero
The run failed and no successful reconciliation was completed.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR systemd (1),
.BR systemd.timer (5)
